```

### ğŸ“¥ Capture Options:
- `-i [interface]` â€“ capture on specific network interface  
- `-w [file_name]` â€“ write capture to file  
- `-r [file_name]` â€“ read packets from file  
- `-c [count]` â€“ capture limited number  
- `-n` â€“ donâ€™t resolve IP addresses  
- `-nn` â€“ donâ€™t resolve IP or protocol numbers  
- `-v`, `-vv`, `-vvv` â€“ verbose output  

### ğŸ§ª Filter Options:
- `host [IP]` â€“ filter by host  
- `src host [IP]`, `dst host [IP]` â€“ filter by source/destination  
- `port [port]`, `src port`, `dst port`  
- `[protocol]` â€“ e.g. ip, ip6, icmp  
- `greater [length]`, `less [length]`  
- `[proto[expr:size]]` â€“ reference specific header byte  
- `[tcp[tcpflags]]` â€“ match TCP flags (SYN, ACK, FIN, etc.)

### ğŸ‘ï¸ Display Options:
- `-q` â€“ brief output  
- `-e` â€“ show MAC header  
- `-A` â€“ ASCII output  
- `-xx` â€“ Hex format  
- `-X` â€“ Hex & ASCII

